{"TopicId":137335,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"The Grand KSP 1.1 Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"KasperVld","CreatedById":40700,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-19T16:43:48Z","PageNum":13,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"John FX","CreatedById":59415,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T13:47:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStoked for stock 64 bit, now it is just the wait for the mods to be updated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0060m not holding my breath for RO although when it drops I\u0060ll have to remember to breathe...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmight take a break now until more mods come out, I have sent off my Pluto probes and finished the RP-0 tree, real life could do with some attention.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Basto","CreatedById":158312,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T13:53:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI played a little in the prerelease but didn\u0027t want to start a campaign until release came out. \u00A0Started my new campaign last night and had a blast. Also did not run into a single issue. I suspect many\u00A0of the problems (granted not all) are coming from mods.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ndiver","CreatedById":60662,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:02:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222524693\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461151614\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Atlas2342\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Atlas2342 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUmm guys, the navball....did it get bigger or am I just lacking sleep. It seems like\u00A0its distracting for me...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt got bigger, also the upper bar. And if you downscale the UI size in the Settings, the buttons on left and right get smaller too (too small to be easily readable)\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mellow:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_mellow.png\u0022 title=\u0022:mellow:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-20T14:03:10Z\u0022 title=\u002204/20/2016 02:03  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by ndiver\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:06:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222524693\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461151614\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155194\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Atlas2342\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Atlas2342 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUmm guys, the navball....did it get bigger or am I just lacking sleep. It seems like\u00A0its distracting for me...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222524967\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461160946\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002260662\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ndiver\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, ndiver said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt got bigger, also the upper bar. And if you downscale the UI size in the Settings, the buttons on left and right get smaller too (too small to be easily readable)\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mellow:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_mellow.png\u0022 title=\u0022:mellow:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee the last link in my signature\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:09:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is it so hard to produce a mathematically flat surface? Or is it more to do with weird craft-surface interactions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atlas2342","CreatedById":155194,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:10:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222524978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461161189\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee the last link in my signature\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMe needs this...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ndiver","CreatedById":60662,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:13:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222524978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461161189\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee the last link in my signature\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, I share, some friends will be happy ;-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"A_name","CreatedById":134040,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:17:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222524174\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461124724\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161286\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Terensky\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Terensky said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nArsonide explained somewhere that the landing legs behave as wheels (indeed they are) and this behaviour is to be expected. So it\u0027s not considered a bug (as now). So I guess it\u0027s also normal, though in my opinion not desiderable, that vessels on landing legs slide on\u00A0slopes, even if I must admit that in the latest release the legs slide way less than before, usually coming to a stop after a short while. It\u0027s still possible though that a kerbal on EVA touching one will be launched in air\u00A0(I did try with the LT-2 on the Mun, don\u0027t know if LT-1 and LT-05 have the same problem). And it\u0027s also possible to turn a landed vessel on legs easily using SAS with Q and E key: if I remember correctly this was not easy to do in 1.05.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFound the relevant thread:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/137333-1228-lt-2-landing-strut-on-the-mun/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/137333-1228-lt-2-landing-strut-on-the-mun/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey actually mention the sliding in the readme.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222524565\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461145998\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002283414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Warpedone\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Warpedone said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery excited about 1.1 but it\u0027s finally overwhelmed the memory on my asthmatic old PC...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mellow:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_mellow.png\u0022 title=\u0022:mellow:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m used to the game crashing every half an hour\u00A0with a dozen interplanetary missions\u00A0out there after a few game years, but now it\u0027s happening by launch 3!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA bit disappointing with all the talk of the new platform being less resource hungry but that\u0027s life, time to start saving for a new machine\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe obvious but are you sure you\u0027re on the x64 version? I downloaded from the KSP store and found I had to manually open the x64 exe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:20:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is flat, but becaude of the curve of Kerbin underneath the\u00A0perfectly flat runway, you actually roll towards the middle. To prevent that happening, the runway should actually be ever so slightly curved to match the planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:34:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222524984\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461161358\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is it so hard to produce a mathematically flat surface? Or is it more to do with weird craft-surface interactions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou mentioned the scary word your self.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease define a \u003Cstrong\u003Emathematically flat surface\u003C/strong\u003E ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m an engineer, if it looks flat enough it\u0027s flat, but for a mathematician ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(My sons are sysdevs, they have told me that coding is math, but I\u0027m in denial).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:35:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525012\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461162039\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is flat, but becaude of the curve of Kerbin underneath the\u00A0perfectly flat runway, you actually roll towards the middle. To prevent that happening, the runway should actually be ever so slightly curved to match the planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, same question, why is it so hard to produce an appropriately curved surface so that it is flat in a practical sense?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:38:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525048\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461162916\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, same question, why is it so hard to produce an appropriately curved surface so that it is flat in a practical sense?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause Kerbin is too small. \u00A0Gravity, man. \u00A0Gravity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:43:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461162852\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou mentioned the scary word your self.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease define a \u003Cstrong\u003Emathematically flat surface\u003C/strong\u003E ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m an engineer, if it looks flat enough it\u0027s flat, but for a mathematician ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(My sons are sysdevs, they have told me that coding is math, but I\u0027m in denial).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did think I\u0027d catch more flack for that \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0yeah I know the scary word is not often practical in the real world, but I figured if it was possible anywhere, it\u0027d be possible inside a software world where everything is mathematically defined...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525053\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461163138\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022regex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, regex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause Kerbin is too small. \u00A0Gravity, man. \u00A0Gravity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you don\u0027t roll around on \u0022flat\u0022 bits of terrain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Choctofliatrio2.0","CreatedById":154657,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:44:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525063\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461163414\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did think I\u0027d catch more flack for that \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0yeah I know the scary word is not often practical in the real world, but I figured if it was possible anywhere, it\u0027d be possible inside a software world where everything is mathematically defined...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you don\u0027t roll around on \u0022flat\u0022 bits of terrain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s kinda counterintuitive. The \u0022flat\u0022 terrain is curved to Kerbin\u0027s curve. Ironically, this makes them flatter than the runway, which is actually flat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:46:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525066\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461163489\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Choctofliatrio2.0\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Choctofliatrio2.0 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s kinda counterintuitive. The \u0022flat\u0022 terrain is curved to Kerbin\u0027s curve. Ironically, this makes them flatter than the runway, which is actually flat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats the picture Im getting - but if this is the case, why make the runway flat? And not \u0022curved to kerbins curve\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:50:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525048\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461162916\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, same question, why is it so hard to produce an appropriately curved surface so that it is flat in a practical sense?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause practical and obvious isn\u0027t the same.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd more due to the fact that Squad (or actually Harvester) decided to use an existing game engine to deliver something useful in 6 months.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat choice will always come back at bite their behinds, but without that choice there wouldn\u0027t been any KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could have written a better core than Harvester did.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it would have taken me 10\u002B years and my employer wouldn\u0027t have paid me to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP like all other good software is a mish-mash of good intentions, brilliance and random chance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:55:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461163828\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause practical and obvious isn\u0027t the same.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd more due to the fact that Squad (or actually Harvester) decided to use an existing game engine to deliver something useful in 6 months.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat choice will always come back at bite their behinds, but without that choice there wouldn\u0027t been any KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could have written a better core than Harvester did.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it would have taken me 10\u002B years and my employer wouldn\u0027t have paid me to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP like all other good software is a mish-mash of good intentions, brilliance and random chance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo it boils down to \u0022complications in the core code\u0022? I mean thats fair enough, was just wondering \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey couldn\u0027t just \u0022paint\u0022 a runway onto the regular surface?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh,\u00A0this must be why the runway has like those hill at either end!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Choctofliatrio2.0","CreatedById":154657,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:55:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525070\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461163563\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats the picture Im getting - but if this is the case, why make the runway flat? And not \u0022curved to kerbins curve\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood question. Maybe they\u0027ll fix it later, or maybe they tried curving it and it didn\u0027t work so they set it aside.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T14:56:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525063\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461163414\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you don\u0027t roll around on \u0022flat\u0022 bits of terrain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy would you? \u00A0They\u0027re curved to the planet. \u00A0If you had a perfectly,\u00A0mathematically straight runway stretching some 21 km sitting on a perfectly,\u00A0gravitationally\u00A0circular part of Earth\u00A0it would be tilted slightly downwards at one end and tilted slightly up at the other, relative to take off direction. \u00A0Scale that down to Kerbin and you get our current situation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-20T14:56:39Z\u0022 title=\u002204/20/2016 02:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by regex\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Padishar","CreatedById":97386,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T15:01:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe runway also slopes to the right along the whole of its length. \u00A0Some more discussion of this from some time ago...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/75960-sideways-slope-of-ksc-runway/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T15:01:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525093\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461164115\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo it boils down to \u0022complications in the core code\u0022? I mean thats fair enough, was just wondering \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey couldn\u0027t just \u0022paint\u0022 a runway onto the regular surface?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh,\u00A0this must be why the runway has like those hill at either end!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt comes down to a very dark part of a coders, dev, project leads heart.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis sucks, but it would take to much to fix, so we have to allow it to ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027re been there you know it, if you haven\u0027t be sure that you will.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"I_Killed_Jeb","CreatedById":84817,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T15:04:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525070\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461163563\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002274091\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022p1t1o\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, p1t1o said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats the picture Im getting - but if this is the case, why make the runway flat? And not \u0022curved to kerbins curve\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause they made it \u0022mathematically flat\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"captaincza738","CreatedById":160959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T15:09:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI AM SO HAPPY!!!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow I must wait for BD Armoury and all the mods to update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T15:09:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525117\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461164654\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284817\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022I_Killed_Jeb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, I_Killed_Jeb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause they made it \u0022mathematically flat\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll use that quote on the pub and many will understand, but then I do have sad friends,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-20T15:13:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222525131\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461164979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll use that quote on the pub and many will understand, but then I do have sad friends,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAround here, we call those \u0022awesome friends\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}